Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of similar to 200 nm-thick gadolinium-doped ceria (GDC) thin films deposited at various substrate temperatures by radio-frequency sputtering was evaluated in a temperature range of 400 degrees C-550 degrees C as an electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells operated at low temperatures.
Titulo: On the reduced electrical conductivity of radio-frequency sputtered doped ceria thin film by elevating the substrate temperature

Sentencas: Morphological, chemical, and crystalline properties were discussed to determine the electrical conductivity; in particular, the electrical conductivity of GDC thin film deposited at 300 degrees C was appreciably lower than that of GDC thin film deposited at 150 degrees C.
Titulo: On the reduced electrical conductivity of radio-frequency sputtered doped ceria thin film by elevating the substrate temperature

Sentencas: The columnar grain boundaries and the reduced ceria formed during the sputtering process are considered as the major factors leading to the measured results.
Titulo: On the reduced electrical conductivity of radio-frequency sputtered doped ceria thin film by elevating the substrate temperature
